SOP: Endpoint DLP Enablement & Operations
Purpose
Extend DLP protections to user devices to reduce exfiltration risk (USB, unsanctioned apps/sites, clipboard, printing, remote sessions). 
Inputs
•	Endpoint population + prerequisites + onboarding method (scripts/MDM/GPO equivalents) 
•	Endpoint control goals (monitor vs block) 
Process
1.	Pre Implementation Checks
o	Identify sensitive data on endpoints to protect 
o	Stakeholder alignment on scope/objectives 
o	Ensure licensing/permissions as required in your environment 
2.	Onboard Devices
o	Choose onboarding approach (local scripts/central policy/MDM equivalent) 
o	Ensure proxy/network settings are compatible
3.	Configure Endpoint DLP Settings (Control Surface)
o	Browser restrictions + removable media/Bluetooth controls + “just in time” evaluation concept 
4.	Define Endpoint Policies
o	Conditions (data + context + action) + monitoring activities + actions 
5.	Pilot + Feedback + Gradual Rollout
o	Pilot group first, analyze feedback, expand in phases to avoid disruption 
6.	Operate: Monitor and Respond
o	Review endpoint activity events and alerts; adjust scope/detection/actions as needed 
Endpoint Activity Coverage (from your notes)
Use these as a checklist of actions to decide: audit vs warn vs block.  
•	Upload to restricted domains / unallowed browsers 
•	Paste to browsers 
•	Copy to clipboard/USB/network share
•	Copy via unallowed Bluetooth apps
•	Copy via RDP 
•	Create/rename sensitive items 
•	Print (including virtual) 
•	Access by restricted apps 
Outputs
•	Endpoint DLP deployment record: pilot scope, controls enabled, restricted actions, monitoring dashboard/alert route, tuning log. 
